it.simonedegiacomi.goboxapi.client

Class GBClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.simonedegiacomi.goboxapi.client.GBClient
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    StandardGBClient

    public abstract class GBClient
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the interface of the goboxclient api and define the basic operation that a client can do.

      • getInfo

        public abstract GBFile getInfo(GBFile file)
                        throws ClientException
        Return a new GBFile with the info retrieved from the storage. If the file is not found a null pointer will be returned. The exception is thrown if there's some connection error. When the file is missing i return a null pointer instead throwing a new exception because you can call this method to check if a file exist, so a null pointer can be a logical value (exist or not).
        Parameters:
        file - File to look at
        Returns:
        GBFile with the storage information
        Throws:
        ClientException - Exception if there some problem with the communication to the storage

      • getFile

        public void getFile(GBFile file)
             throws ClientException,
                    java.io.IOException
        Retrieve the file from the storage and save it to the file position saved inside the GBFile passed as argument. If the file doesn't exist a new exception is thrown. This method automatically create needed directory to store the file, calling the mkdirs java File method. NOTE that this method is an alias for getFile(GBFile, OutputStream) so this file must have a valid id. Also remember that this method use the path (and the prefix) of the argument file, so is recommended to pass a file retrieved via getInfo(GBFile).
        Parameters:
        file - File to retrieve.
        Throws:
        ClientException - Exception thrown in case of invalid id, network error or io error while saving the file to the disk
        java.io.IOException

      • getFile

        public abstract void getFile(GBFile file,
                             java.io.OutputStream dst)
                      throws ClientException,
                             java.io.IOException
        Download the specified file ito the specified output stream. The argument file of this method must know his ID. If you have only the path use the getInfo(GBFile) method first. NOTE that this method doesn't close the stream
        Parameters:
        file - File to download
        dst - Destination of the input stream of the file
        Throws:
        ClientException - Exception thrown in case of invalid id or network error
        java.io.IOException
